perience of having his or her feelings, dignity, and mind respected,"), mdx("p", null, "Adults do possess greater knowledge than children. The question is, How is this knowledge to be transmitted?"), mdx("p", null, "No one who is terrified of making mistakes can attain moral autonomy."), mdx("p", null, "to honor our internal signals to that extent\u2014is to practice the ultimate form of intellectual independence,"), mdx("p", null, "When the price of harmony with others becomes the surrender of our mind, an autonomous individual chooses not to pay it."), mdx("p", null, "So: fear of autonomy entails fear of self-responsibility entails fear of identity entails fear of aloneness entails fear of death."), mdx("h3", {
